        "id": 1,
        "name": "Paucartambo",
        "description": "The Tres Cruces viewpoint at dawn — watching the sunrise over the Amazon basin from 3,700 meters.\n\nWe left Paucartambo at 3am, driving the winding mountain road in complete darkness. The temperature dropped steadily as we climbed, and by the time we reached the viewpoint it was close to freezing. A handful of other travelers huddled together in the dark, wrapped in blankets, waiting.\n\nThen the sky began to change. First a thin orange line on the horizon, then layers of pink and gold spreading across the cloud sea below. The Amazon basin stretched endlessly beneath us — an ocean of clouds with islands of distant peaks poking through. The locals call this the 'balcony over the jungle,' and standing there at 3,700 meters watching the sun rise over an infinite green carpet, I understood why.",
